,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n20079"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AA%D9%8E%D8%B3%D8%A7%D9%82%D9%8E%D8%B7%D9%8E"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to fall down successively or gradually","examples":[{"text":"بَدَأَ الْمَطَرُ يَتَسَاقَطُ. أَغْمَضَتْ عَيْنَيْهَا.","english":"The rain started to fall down. She shut her eyes."}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to die one by one in a quick manner.","tags":["figuratively"],"examples":[{"text":"وَعَلَىٰ اَلْأَرْضِ تَسَاقَطْنَا لِنُعْلِي عَلَمًا","english":"and on the ground we fell one by one to uphold a flag"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of تَسَاقَطَ (tasāqaṭa) (form VI)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From the root س ق ط (s q ṭ), to fall."},"ipa":["/ta.saː.qa.tˤa/","/ta.saː.qutˤ/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n20079","headword_ar":"تساقط","root":"sqT","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see its variation"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ais~aAqaTa","text_ar":"اِسَّاقَطَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in 1; first sentence. ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It fell in consecutive portions"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quantities"},{"kind":"text","text":"[like the leaves of a tree, &c.;"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by degrees; gradually"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (M, K.) A poet says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"kanajomi Alv~uray~aA waA^amoTaArihaA \n                      \n                     \n                        wayawomK tasaAqaTu la*~aAtuhu"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e. (assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Many a day"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of which the pleasures come one thing after another;"},{"kind":"text","text":"[such a day being"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"like the asterism of the Pleiades, and"},{"kind":"text","text":"the pleasures thereof like"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"its rains;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] meaning the abounding of its pleasures. (TA.) And you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tasaAqaTa A_ilaY~a","text_ar":"تَسَاقَطَ اـِلَىَّ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xayoru fulaAnK","text_ar":"خَيْرُ فُلَانٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The wealth of such a one fell,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"came, to me, one thing after another"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tsAqT EalaY Al$~aYN'i","text_ar":"تساقط عَلَى الشَّىٌءِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He threw himself upon the thing."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tsAqT EalaY Alr~ajuli yaqiyh","text_ar":"تساقط عَلَى الرَّجُلِ يَقِيه"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"binafosihi","text_ar":"بِنَفْسِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He threw himself upon the man, protecting him with his own person"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}